<h1>Pagination</h1>
<p class="text-muted mb-1">
  The gem doesn't paginate on its own (no surprise row limits). You paginate in
  the controller with your own gem — here
  <a href="https://github.com/kaminari/kaminari">kaminari</a> — and because a
  kaminari-paginated relation carries its page state,
  <code>crud_collection</code> notices and renders the footer pager
  automatically. The whole integration is two lines
  (<a href="https://github.com/itadventurer/crud_components/blob/main/test/dummy/app/controllers/pagination_controller.rb">controller</a>):
</p>
<pre class="bg-body-tertiary border rounded p-3 small mb-3"><code>@query = CrudComponents::Query.new(Book, params, ability: current_ability)
@books = @query.apply(Book.all).page(params[:page]).per(15)   # kaminari</code></pre>

<p class="text-muted small">
  120 seeded books, 15 per page. Filtering, search and sort still work — the
  pager's <code>?page=</code> is a plain GET param, so it composes with the
  gem's own filter params. Try sorting a column, then turning the page.
</p>

<%= crud_collection @books, query: @query %>   <%# the footer pager renders itself %>
